Patient Waitlist Analysis Dashboard | Power BI

## Project Overview

This project focuses on analyzing healthcare patient waitlist data using Power BI to identify trends, monitor performance, and support data-driven decision-making.
The dashboard provides a comprehensive view of patient waitlists across different specialties, age groups, and case types, enabling stakeholders to understand 
demand patterns and resource allocation requirements.

## Objectives

* Analyze patient waitlist volumes across medical specialties.
* Compare current waitlist trends with the previous year's performance.
* Identify specialties experiencing the highest patient backlog.
* Monitor monthly variations in waitlist numbers.
* Provide actionable insights for operational planning and capacity management.

## Data Preparation & Transformation

* Cleaned and transformed raw healthcare datasets using Power Query.
* Handled missing values and standardized data formats.
* Combined multiple tables to create a unified data model.
* Performed data validation and quality checks to ensure reporting accuracy.

## Dashboard Features

* Specialty-wise patient waitlist analysis.
* Monthly and yearly trend comparison.
* Current month vs previous year same-month performance tracking.
* Age profile and case type segmentation.
* Interactive filters and drill-down capabilities for detailed analysis.

## DAX Measures Used

* CALCULATE()
* SUM()
* AVERAGE()
* MEDIAN()
* SWITCH()
* IF()
* ISBLANK()

## Key Insights

* Identified an approximately 11% year-over-year increase in patient waitlist volume.
* Highlighted specialties with consistently high waiting lists requiring operational attention.
* Enabled comparison of historical and current performance trends.
* Improved visibility into patient demand patterns across healthcare services.

## Tools & Technologies

* Power BI
* DAX
* Power Query
* Microsoft Excel
* Data Modeling & Data Visualization

## Business Impact

The dashboard helps healthcare administrators monitor patient waitlists effectively, identify bottlenecks, optimize resource allocation, 
and make informed decisions to improve patient service delivery and reduce waiting times.
